## Review Focus
- If the draft opens with submission-form or title-page metadata (student name line, course code, course title, assignment title as an administrative block), remove it entirely; keep only the essay title and scholarly body.
- Fix grammar, spelling, and awkward phrasing.
- Improve clarity and precision: replace weak or vague phrasing with better phrasing of similar length rather than deleting content.
- Preserve the plan's section order, section boundaries, and custom headings. If the plan reflects a user-specified structure, keep that structure intact.
- Headings must be plain text with `#` markers only — remove any `**` or `*` wrapping from headings.
- Preserve **every** existing `[[source_id]]` marker — do NOT remove, drop, or merge them away when tightening prose; do NOT replace them with literal `(Author, Year)` text.
- Do **not** reduce how many **distinct** sources are cited unless you are fixing a clear factual or formatting error.
- Do NOT add a References/Βιβλιογραφία section.
- Preserve the argument structure, tone, and register — improve expression, do not dramatize or intensify.
- Do NOT merge, split, reorder, or rename sections unless the change is purely superficial formatting normalisation.
- Do NOT add vivid, dramatic, or rhetorical flourishes not present in the draft.

